{"id": 231263558, "title": "1 dead after overnight crash, fire in Suffolk", "text": "A person died early Saturday morning following a tractor crash and fire in Suffolk, according to Suffolk Fire & Rescue. Suffolk crews were dispatched to the 4400 block of Holland Road shortly before 3 a.m., following a reported power line down and brush on fire. Upon arrival, Engine 7 upgraded the response due to a large fire in the area. As Engine 7\u2019s crews started to attack the fire, they spotted a tractor that had been hauling a shipping container on fire. The tractor had left the roadway and struck several trees. The tractor was on fire, but the shipping container \u2014 which had overturned \u2014 was not. Crews determined the fire was under control at 3:30 a.m. Once the fire was out, firefighters located one person deceased in the cab of the tractor. The saddle tank had ruptured. Firefighters are working to identify the contents of the shipping container, but the contents of the shipping container were not involved in the fire and are not a hazard, Suffolk Fire & Rescue reports. Suffolk Police are investigating the cause of the crash, and the Fire Marshal\u2019s Office is investigating the cause and origin of the fire. Josh Janney, joshua.janney@virginiamedia.com", "summary": "A person died early Saturday morning following a tractor crash and fire at the 4400 block of Holland Road, Suffolk Fire &#38; Rescue report.", "url": "https://www.pilotonline.com/2024/06/08/1-person-dead-after-overnight-crash-fire-in-suffolk/", "image": "https://www.pilotonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Holland-Fire-June-8-2024-2.jpg?w=1024", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 13:34:22", "author": "Josh Janney", "authors": ["Josh Janney"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": -0.846}